The Nasarawa State Command of the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corp (NSCDC), Wednesday, paraded a 73-year-old man for allegedly defiling a three-year-old girl. Ali Isa, a father of 11 children with two wives, was arrested by officers of NSCDC on Tuesday at Kandare in Kokona Local Government Area of Nasarawa State. Parading the suspect yesterday at the NSCDC Command headquarters in Lafia, the state capital, the Commandant, Alhaji Mahmaoud Gidado-Fari, said that the suspect was arrested following a man hunt. He disclosed that the suspect had confessed to the crime and would be taken to court to face prosecution. The Commandant disclosed that the girl was receiving treatment at a hospital for injuries she sustained during the incident. When asked what moved him in committing the alleged crime during an interview, the suspect blamed Satan. He appealed to the authorities to temper justice with mercy, saying this was the first time of committing such crime.